            <h3 data-uuid="05f44d4fcbdb4c60a18cb6973c3da76d">Part 2: Write an Informative Essay</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="16ec7fa4542340558c04d098c755dcfb">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="03b03c4d001e463ab2b6d01ceef70cc1">World
                War I began when Archduke Ferdinand was assassinated in 1914. For over four
                years, the Central powers (including Austria-Hungary and Germany) fought the
                Allied powers (including France, Russia, and Britain). The U.S. joined in 1917.
                The Allies won, resulting in an armistice in November 1918.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="ca7e6caba64746929d4a8a55a867fd33">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="c4a73751af3b4022883b47668d0a14cd">When World War I broke out in Europe in 1914, President Woodrow Wilson declared U.S. neutrality. In an informative essay, explain how the United States went from a neutral party, to a member of the Allies, to a member of the winning side that nonetheless did not sign the Treaty of Versailles.</p>
            <p data-uuid="51df532d686246aeb57fa7d830f44c17"></p>
            <p data-uuid="9291d5c2ede3454d9cbc95d1e19564f7">Complete the following steps as you plan and compose your essay.</p>
            <ol data-uuid="2ea00e04f0b342d4ba1c9487b5af297b">
                <li data-uuid="9d680ce5df4c47ef83ae4a1a06cb64b4">Review your notes and sources before you start writing.</li>
                <li data-uuid="9c7d37900dc848058a87918d4d43e2e0">Use at least <i>three</i> of the sources in Part 1, and develop the topic with relevant, well-chosen text or visual evidence from the documents.</li>
                <li data-uuid="c98cda7484464e3eb4527cc1d1e103cf">Cite specific text or visual evidence from each of the sources in your response.</li>
                <li data-uuid="d6499fa2e65548deb02f542859daae81">Plan your essay so that it includes an introduction, several body paragraphs, and a concluding paragraph.</li>
                <li data-uuid="dca80fbea417499c91d0193d01813dad">Organize your essay in a clear and logical
                    way that focuses on the topic and supports it with explanations and facts.</li>
                <li data-uuid="874cd2a2a7884f18bf55b8be16fb664e">Write a conclusion that sums up your ideas and supports the information you present.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
